  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "HS",
    "text": "This is the Spitz family before the war in Munkacs. It was probably made in 1937 or '38. I don't remember exactly when. And this is my parents, my mother and father, and this is the brother I lost in the gas chambers in the concentration camps in Auschwitz. And this is my sister, but she died after liberation in Sweden of tuberculosis. And this is a family, my mother's sister's family, which only one child survived, the youngest one. And he lives in London, England, now. And he's married, and he has a daughter. The rest of the family all perished. And some of the children were married and had children, already grandchildren, the parents. So it's a shame. They were very, very orthodox, religious, nice people.",
